ilteredState(...)` pres...\",\n90:         \"`renderSearchBar` and `usesLocalSearchState()` keep only route-local query state without any preference persistence.\",\n91:         \"`renderSearchBar` feeds route-level query state into `HomeStore.buildFilteredState(...)` and `HistoryStore.buildVisibleState(...)`, enabling immediate home/history filtering from the shared search surface.\",\n92:         \"`buildHistoryRoute` reloads `HistoryStore.buildVisibleState(...)` on each route render so the current liked-restaurant state is reflected whenever the page is entered or updated.\",\n93:         \"`HistoryStore` plus `FoodikeBootstrap` route state expose observable search/tab state and reload the repository-backed favourites list on each rebuild.\",\n94:         \"`bootstrap_page.cj` keeps `homeSelectedFilter` in route state, and `buildFilterRow` re-renders selected styling while `HomeStore.buildFilteredState(...)` applies the active chip to visible lists.\",\n95:         \"`FoodikeBootstrap::buildHistoryRoute` binds current query/tab state and recomputes `HistoryStore.buildVisibleState(...)` whenever the history route is shown.\",\n96:         \"`HistoryPageState` and the route-local history state fields keep equivalent plain state for favourites, records, query, and tab selection without any permission handling.\"\n97:       ],\n98:       \"acceptanceEvidence\": [\n99:         \"Replace broad endpoints with precise target functions, types, resources, or tests before closing the group.\"\n100:       ],\n101:       \"riskHints\": [\n102:         \"current evidence uses broad shell/root/whole-file endpoints\"\n103:       ],\n104:       \"matrixRows\": [\n105:         {\n106:           \"kind\": \"source-feature\",\n107:           \"featureId\": \"app-src-main-java-com-example-foodike-presentation-home-ef0657c4ea-005-screen-lifecycle-entry-point-initializat\",\n108:           \"featureName\": \"Screen lifecycle, entry point initialization, resume/pause refresh, or teardow