Info(800), \"50+\")\n81:         @Assert(getCustomerInfo(12), \"1000+\")\n82:     }\n83: \n84:     @TestCase\n85:     public func historyStoreSelectionSavesRestaurantBeforeNavigation(): Unit {\n86:         let store = HistoryStore()\n87:         let restaurant = store.loadHistoryState().favourites[1]\n88:         let events = ArrayList<String>([])\n89:         store.selectRestaurant(restaurant, { =>\n90:             events.add(store.session().getSelectedRestaurantName())\n91:             events.add(\"navigate\")\n92:         })\n93:         @Assert(events[0], restaurant.name)\n94:         @Assert(events[1], \"navigate\")\n95:     }\n96: \n97:     @TestCase\n98:     public func historyStoreExposesSourceTabOrdering(): Unit {\n99:         let store = HistoryStore()\n100:         @Assert(store.tabLabelText(0), \"History\")\n101:         @Assert(store.tabLabelText(1), \"Favourites\")\n102:     }\n103: \n104:     @TestCase\n105:     public func historyStoreFiltersFavouriteRestaurantsFromSearchQuery(): Unit {\n106:         let store = HistoryStore()\n107:         let state = store.buildVisibleState(\"Mission\")\n108:         @Assert(state.favourites.size, 2)\n109:         @Assert(state.favourites[0].place, \"Mission Charali\")\n110:         @Assert(state.favourites[1].place, \"Mission Charali\")\n111:     }\n112: \n113:     @TestCase\n114:     public func historyStoreSearchIsCaseInsensitiveForLikedRestaurants(): Unit {\n115:         let store = HistoryStore()\n116:         let state = store.buildVisibleState(\"mission\")\n117:         @Assert(state.favourites.size, 2)\n118:         @Assert(state.favourites[0].place, \"Mission Charali\")\n119:     }\n120: }\n\n(End of file - total 120 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"package ohos_app_cangjie_entry_test\n\nimport ohos_app_cangjie_entry.ohos_app_cangjie_entry.features.home.HomeStore\nimport ohos_app_cangjie_entry.ohos_app_cangjie_entry.features.history.HistoryStore\nimport ohos_app_cangjie_entry.ohos_app_cangjie_ent